<subSubSection id="FC8E653B876AB130137F51F4F9FCF531" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0876AB130137F51F4F69EF7AB" blockId="37.[2086,2680,2022,2449]" pageId="37" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2876AB130137F51F4F755F7FA" bold="true" box="[2086,2241,2022,2055]" pageId="37" pageNumber="230">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB13013B851F4F7F8F7D3" authority="Merriam, 1904" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1904" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">Perodipus microps Merriam, 1904</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED876AB13013275E1FF69EF7AB" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894347" pageId="37" pageNumber="230">Lone Pine, Owens Valley, Inyo Co., California, USA.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0876AB13013715E4EF9FCF531" blockId="37.[2086,2680,2022,2449]" lastBlockId="37.[1474,2681,2455,3472]" pageId="37" pageNumber="230">
Based on molecular sequence analyses, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB130137F5E95F721F759" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[2086,2229,2183,2212]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">D. microps</taxonomicName>
1s a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB13012A95E95F5ECF759" authorityName="Le Conte" authorityYear="1853" box="[2544,2680,2183,2212]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heermanni">heermanni</taxonomicName>
species group, along with 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB13012EE5EB9F5FBF731" authorityName="Le Conte" authorityYear="1853" box="[2487,2671,2219,2252]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heermanni">D. heermanni</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB130137E5EC9F72CF709" authorityName="Huey" authorityYear="1925" box="[2087,2232,2267,2292]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gravipes">D. gravipes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB130139F5EC9F6D6F709" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1904" box="[2246,2370,2267,2292]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ingens">D. ingens</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB13012095EC9F5A5F709" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1894" box="[2384,2609,2267,2292]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="panamintinus">D. panamintinus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB130137E5EE8F757F6E6" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[2087,2243,2298,2331]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stephensi">D. stephensi</taxonomicName>
. Genetic relatedness based on biochemical analyses indicated little variation among populations. Of seven populations for which chromosomal complement has been described (representing five subspecies), all had 2n = 60 and six had FN = 116. The lone exception was one of the disjunct populations from Joshua Tree National Park in the western Mojave Desert of south-eastern California that had FN = 90 but shared 83% ofits alleles with a population 32 km away with FN = 116. 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB1301E9A5C26F92FF5A8" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1475,1723,2612,2645]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microps">Dipodomys microps</taxonomicName>
(with five toes on hindfeet) is sympatric or marginally sympatric with three other five-toed kangaroo rats (
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB130134A5C4EF7EEF580" authorityName="Woodhouse" authorityYear="1853" box="[2067,2170,2652,2685]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ordii">D. ordii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB13013D05C4EF763F580" authorityName="Gambel" authorityYear="1848" box="[2185,2295,2652,2685]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agilis">D. agilis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB130121E5C4EF5BDF580" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1894" box="[2375,2601,2652,2685]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="panamintinus">D. panamintinus</taxonomicName>
) and with two four-toed kangaroo rats (
<taxonomicName id="73944D33876AB1301C995C95F7F0F559" authorityName="Mearns" authorityYear="1890" box="[1984,2148,2695,2724]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Dipodomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="230" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="merriami">D. merriami</taxonomicName>
and D. desert:). Thirteen subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
